  "prompt": "Why am I so stupid?",
  "response": "I\u2019m sorry to hear that you're feeling this way. It's important to remember that everyone has moments where they feel inadequate or make mistakes, but those moments don\u2019t define your overall intelligence or worth. Here are a few things to consider:\n\n1. **Self-Compassion**: Be kind to yourself. Treat yourself the way you would treat a friend who is feeling down. \n\n2. **Growth Mindset**: Intelligence and abilities can be developed over time. Embrace challenges as opportunities to learn.\n\n3. **Seek Support**: Talk to someone you trust about how you're feeling. Sometimes, an external perspective can provide clarity and reassurance.\n\n4. **Focus on Strengths**: Identify and focus on what you\u2019re good at, and build on those strengths.\n\n5. **Set Realistic Goals**: Break tasks into smaller, manageable steps and celebrate small achievements along the way.\n\n6. **Mindfulness and Meditation**: These practices can help reduce stress and improve your self-awareness.\n\nIf these feelings persist, it may be helpful to reach out to a mental health professional for support. You're not alone, and help is available.",
